Full Title: Modern Language Association 
Short Title: MLA 

Date: 27-Dec-2008 - 30-Dec-2008
Location: San Francisco, CA, USA 
Contact Person: Matthew Juge
Meeting Email: mattjuge@txstate.edu
Web Site: http://uweb.txstate.edu/~mj13 

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Language Family(ies): Romance 

Call Deadline: 17-Mar-2008 

Meeting Description:

We invite submissions on any aspect of Romance linguistics, especially those with a comparative approach. 

Call for Papers

We solicit abstracts on Romance linguistics in any subfield of linguistics (e.g., phonetics, phonology, morphology, syntax, semantics, sociolinguistics, anthropological linguistics, etc.), including philological studies. Abstracts with a comparative approach will be given special preference.

Presentations are 20 minutes.

Abstracts should be no more than one page (12 point font, 1-inch margins).

Deadline for receipt of abstracts: March 17, 2008.

Electronic submissions (as .pdf files) are preferred. Please send electronic submissions to the e-mail address below.

Contact information:
Matthew L. Juge
Department of Modern Languages
Texas State University-San Marcos
601 University Dr.
San Marcos, TX 78666

Telephone: (512) 245-7724
Fax: (512) 245-8298


	
