Linguistic Field(s): Not Applicable 

Call Deadline: 30-Jun-2008 

Meeting Description:

Join academics from all over the world in the beautiful Black Hills for academic presentations, conversation, and relaxation while discussing important issues in International Business.  Listen to an internationally known speaker while enjoying an evening of fine dining, camaraderie, and a stunning view of the monument at the Mount Rushmore Memorial in the Buffalo Dining Room. 

Call for Papers
15th Annual South Dakota International Business Conference
Hosted by: Northern State University

October 9-11, 2008
Rapid City, South Dakota USA
Submission Deadline: June 30, 2008
Conference Web site: www.ibc-nsu.org

Join academics from all over the world in the beautiful Black Hills for academic presentations, conversation, and relaxation while discussing important issues in International Business. Listen to an internationally known speaker while enjoying an evening of fine dining, camaraderie, and a stunning view of the monument at the Mount Rushmore Memorial in the Buffalo Dining Room.  

Abstract submissions are currently being accepted for the 15th Annual South Dakota International Business Conference in scenic Rapid City, S.D.  Abstracts must be submitted before the deadline of June 30, 2008.

All accepted papers will be published in conference proceedings. Abstracts must have an international theme. Suggested topics include: Language Issues Related to Conduct of International Business, Accounting, Business Ethics, Entrepreneurship, Marketing, Not-for-profit, Finance, Teaching/Pedagogy/Administrative Issues, Economics, Management Systems, E-Commerce, Global/Small Business, Tourism, and Social Management Issues.  

Pre-registration prior to September 19, 2008, will save on conference registration fees. Early registration fee includes breakfast and lunch for the duration of the conference, the keynote dinner at Mt. Rushmore National Monument, and proceedings. We encourage authors to submit their abstracts via e-mail. The document should be in Microsoft Word if not included in the body of the e-mail. Please include a cover page with: Title, name, organization address, phone, e-mail address (for each author). Submit abstracts to: ceib@northern.edu 

Conference Web site www.ibc-nsu.org 

Submission of Abstract: June 30, 2008
Notification of Acceptance: July 25, 2008
Full paper submission: September 12, 2008
Conference: October 9-11, 2008

